<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9558] getListOffsetsCalls doesn&apos;t update node in case of leader change</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9558</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As seen here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/admin/KafkaAdminClient.java#L3810&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/admin/KafkaAdminClient.java#L3810&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In handling the response in the `listOffsets` call, if there are errors in the topic partition that require a metadata refresh, it simply passes the call object as `this`. This produces incorrect behavior if there was a leader change, because the call object never gets its leader node updated. This will result in a tight loop of list offsets being called to the same old leader and not resulting in offsets, even though the metadata was correctly updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13285405">KAFKA-9558</key>
