                            <comment id="17037329" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 14 Feb 2020 22:10:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;skaundinya15 commented on pull request #8119: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9558&quot; title=&quot;getListOffsetsCalls doesn&amp;#39;t update node in case of leader change&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-9558&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-9558&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fixing retry logic for getListOffsetsCalls&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/8119&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/8119&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9558&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9558&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   This PR is to fix the retry logic for `getListOffsetsCalls`. Previously, if there were partitions with errors, it would only pass in the current call object to retry after a metadata refresh. However this is incorrect as if there&apos;s a leader change, the call object never gets updated with the correct leader node to query. This PR fixes this by making another call to `getListOffsetsCalls` with only the error topic partitions as the next calls to be made after the metadata refresh. In addition there is an additional test to test the scenario where a leader change occurs.&lt;/p&gt;

